The paper deals with the generation of a secret key and the use of common randomness, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of correlated sources and the characterization of communication rates, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper establishes invariance properties of common information quantities, which is a topic related to statistical learning (cs.SI).
